<p>I have a problem with a plugin and my theme (my featured posts aren't translated after using a translation plugin, PolyLang). Based on the post in the link below, I have to modify my theme template to keep all query vars</p>  <p><a href="https://polylang.wordpress.com/2014/06/12/dont-override-query-vars-with-query_posts-arguments/" rel="nofollow">https://polylang.wordpress.com/2014/06/12/dont-override-query-vars-with-query_posts-arguments/</a></p>  <p>However I am not knowledgeable enough to make the changes based on his sample code. Could you please help me in correcting my template? I am a beginner at this.</p>  <p>Here is the lines of code corresponding with displaying featured posts for my theme (Gateway) from template-home.php.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php  // Get chosen category $home_posts_cat = esc_attr( get_theme_mod( 'home_posts_cat' ) );  // WP_Query arguments $args = array ( 'post_type'         =&gt; 'post', 'cat'               =&gt; $home_posts_cat, 'posts_per_page'    =&gt; '3', 'post__not_in'      =&gt; get_option('sticky_posts'), );  // The Query $query = new WP_Query( $args );  // The Loop if ( $query-&gt;have_posts() ) { while ( $query-&gt;have_posts() ) { $query-&gt;the_post();   get_template_part( 'template-parts/content', 'home' ); }  } else {   get_template_part( 'template-parts/content', 'none' );  } // Restore original Post Data wp_reset_postdata();   ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Thanks a lot!</p>  <p>here is my website for reference: <a href="http://ewaste.my" rel="nofollow">http://ewaste.my</a> </p>